    <div class="results-chart">
      <img src="assets/granite_test_v2.png" alt="DIV2K Granite Test — Channel pair comparison showing KS distribution, variance ratio across cascade, head-to-head comparison, and enrichment ratio" loading="lazy">
      <p class="caption">DIV2K validation: 800 images through Q95 &rarr; Q85 &rarr; Q75 &rarr; Q60 &rarr; Q40 cascade</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Layer Performance Across the Cascade</h3>
    <p>Each layer has a validated operational range. Together they provide defense in depth from embedding through aggressive recompression.</p>

    <h4>Layer D &mdash; Blind Spatial Variance Detection</h4>
    <p>No reference image needed. The image is its own control group. Compression <em>amplifies</em> the variance anomaly at marker positions. Validated on 500 DIV2K images.</p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Generation</th><th>Quality</th><th>G-B KS p&lt;0.05</th><th>R-G KS p&lt;0.05</th><th>G-B Variance Ratio</th><th>Amplification</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Gen 0</td><td>Q95</td><td>96.4%</td><td>90.1%</td><td>1.05</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 1</td><td>Q85</td><td>96.4%</td><td>90.1%</td><td>1.09</td><td class="yes">YES</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 2</td><td>Q75</td><td>94.2%</td><td>87.5%</td><td>1.12</td><td class="yes">YES</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 3</td><td>Q60</td><td>91.8%</td><td>82.3%</td><td>1.15</td><td class="yes">YES</td></tr>
          <tr class="highlight-row"><td>Gen 4</td><td>Q40</td><td>90%+</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>1.18</td><td class="yes">YES</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="caption" style="margin-top:-1rem">Variance ratio increases under compression &mdash; granite under sandstone. KS frequency detection degrades at Q60+ but spatial variance compensates.</p>

    <h4>Layer E &mdash; Spanning Relational Sentinel</h4>
    <p>Relational encoding within 8&times;8 DCT blocks. The differential between correlated pixels survives when absolute values do not. Validated on 500 DIV2K images.</p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Generation</th><th>Quality</th><th>T24 Intact</th><th>Demoted to T16/T8</th><th>Effective Detection</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Gen 0</td><td>Q95</td><td>99.2%</td><td>14.3%</td><td>&gt;99%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 1</td><td>Q85</td><td>98.2%</td><td>8.6%</td><td>&gt;99%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 2</td><td>Q75</td><td>98.0%</td><td>8.5%</td><td>&gt;99%</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 3</td><td>Q60</td><td>98.3%</td><td>14.4%</td><td>&gt;99%</td></tr>
          <tr class="highlight-row"><td>Gen 4</td><td>Q40</td><td>98.6%</td><td>28.4%</td><td>&gt;99%</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="caption" style="margin-top:-1rem">28.4% T24 demotion at Q40 means graceful degradation, not failure &mdash; demoted sentinels are still detected at lower tier.</p>

    <h4>Layer BC &mdash; Compound Frequency Markers</h4>
    <p>Twin-prime compound markers at known positions. Effective at G0&ndash;G2. Frequency signal degrades under aggressive compression &mdash; this is an honest result, not a failure. Layer BC is a near-field detector.</p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Generation</th><th>Quality</th><th>G-B Detection</th><th>R-G Detection</th><th>Status</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Gen 0</td><td>Q95</td><td>96.4%</td><td>90.1%</td><td class="yes">STRONG</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 1</td><td>Q85</td><td>96.4%</td><td>90.1%</td><td class="yes">STRONG</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 2</td><td>Q75</td><td>~90%</td><td>~80%</td><td>DEGRADING</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 3</td><td>Q60</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>UNRELIABLE</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Gen 4</td><td>Q40</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>NOT EFFECTIVE</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

